The paper proposes a neural network system for coreference resolution, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions that the model does not rely on many handcrafted features and is easy to train and use, indicating that it may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning and artificial intelligence, such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of neural networks also suggests that it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions experiments on the English portion of CoNLL 2012 Shared Task, which is a dataset commonly used in NLP research, indicating that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as this sub-category often includes research on NLP tasks.
